snippet: Clemson is No. 1, followed by Alabama; Oklahoma, whose season is over; and Iowa. Michigan State and Ohio State are ranked fifth and sixth.
abstract: Oklahoma, currently No 3 in College Football Playoff rankings, appears to have secured spot in final four with their season over; other teams ranked to win playoff spots discussed.
lead_paragraph: Clemson is No. 1, followed by Alabama; Oklahoma, whose season is over; and Iowa. Michigan State and Ohio State are ranked fifth and sixth.

headline.main: Oklahoma Looks Safe in College Football Playoff Rankings
